%N A098593 A triangle of Krawtchouk coefficients.
%C A098593 Row sums are A009545(n+1), with e.g.f. exp(x)(cos(x)+sin(x)). Diagonal sums are A077948.
%C A098593 The rows are the diagonals of the Krawtchouk matrices. Coincides with the Riordan array (1/(1-x),(1-2x)/(1-x)). - _Paul Barry_, Sep 24 2004
%C A098593 Corresponds to Pascal-(1,-2,1) array, read by antidiagonals. The Pascal-(1,-2,1) array has n-th row generated by (1-2x)^n/(1-x)^(n+1). - _Paul Barry_, Sep 24 2004
%C A098593 A modified version (different signs) of this triangle is given by T(n,k) = Sum_{j=0..n} C(n-k,j)*C(k,j)*cos(Pi*(k-j)). - _Paul Barry_, Jun 14 2007
%D A098593 P. Feinsilver and J. Kocik, Krawtchouk matrices from classical and quantum walks, Contemporary Mathematics, 287 2001, pp. 83-96.
%H A098593 G. C. Greubel, <a href="/A098593/b098593.txt">Table of n, a(n) for the first 50 rows, flattened</a>
%H A098593 Paul Barry, <a href="https://cs.uwaterloo.ca/journals/JIS/VOL11/Barry/barry594.html">A note on Krawtchouk Polynomials and Riordan Arrays</a>, JIS 11 (2008) 08.2.2
%H A098593 P. Feinsilver and J. Kocik, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/quant-ph/0702073">Krawtchouk polynomials and Krawtchouk matrices</a>, arxiv:quant-ph/0702073, 2007.
%F A098593 T(n, k) = Sum_{i=0..k} binomial(n-k, k-i)*binomial(k, i)*(-1)^(k-i), k<=n.
%F A098593 T(n, k) = T(n-1, k) + T(n-1, k-1) - 2*T(n-2, k-1) (n>0). - _Paul Barry_, Sep 24 2004
%F A098593 T(n, k) = [k<=n]*Hypergeometric2F1(-k,k-n;1;-1). - _Paul Barry_, Jan 24 2011
%F A098593 E.g.f. for the n-th subdiagonal: exp(x)*P(n,x), where P(n,x) is the polynomial Sum_{k = 0..n} (-1)^k*binomial(n,k)* x^k/k!. For example, the e.g.f. for the second subdiagonal is exp(x)*(1 - 2*x + x^2/2) = 1 - x - 2*x^2/2! - 2*x^3/3! - x^4/4! + x^5/5! + .... - _Peter Bala_, Mar 05 2017
